you'll figure it out.

02:00.787 --> 02:02.368
I've been
in some rough places,

02:02.497 --> 02:04.237
had a few conversations
with myself.

02:04.374 --> 02:07.958
Eventually I got
where I needed to be.

02:09.630 --> 02:10.870
- And where was that?

02:11.006 --> 02:12.712
- Where I'm standing.

02:12.841 --> 02:14.797
It's always
where I'm standing.

02:14.926 --> 02:17.133
- Does this place
mean something to you?

02:18.680 --> 02:21.057
- You know, sometimes, uh...

02:21.183 --> 02:23.515
you leave a mark
where you've been.

02:23.644 --> 02:26.431
Sometimes the tide
just washes it away.

02:26.563 --> 02:29.600
But you don't know
until you come back, do you?

02:29.733 --> 02:31.564
- So you from around here?

02:31.693 --> 02:33.194
- Yeah...

02:33.320 --> 02:35.151
once upon a time.

02:37.032 --> 02:38.613
Good luck.

02:52.339 --> 02:54.250
[bell rings]

02:54.383 --> 02:56.374
- How can I help you?

02:56.510 --> 02:57.716
- Hello, Dave.

02:57.844 --> 03:00.221
It's been a while.
You miss me?

03:00.347 --> 03:02.804
I missed you.

03:02.933 --> 03:04.013
- How you been, Max?

03:04.142 --> 03:05.928
- Well, I've been pacing
an 8x10-foot cell

03:06.061 --> 03:07.722
for close on 10,000 days.

03:07.854 --> 03:09.230
I haven't eaten
a meal off a plate,

03:09.356 --> 03:12.519
taken a hot shower,
or run a mile since '85.

03:15.362 --> 03:16.317
And you?

03:16.446 --> 03:19.483
- Oh, you know,
still running the paper—

03:19.616 --> 03:21.698
posting ads
for, uh, old dogs

03:21.827 --> 03:24.239
and, uh, lost furniture.

03:24.371 --> 03:26.407
- You're still singing
that same old song, huh?

03:26.540 --> 03:28.451
- What do you want, Max?

03:28.583 --> 03:29.743
Money?

03:32.170 --> 03:35.082
- No, what I want now
is a job.

03:35.215 --> 03:38.548
- Well, I'm not sure
I have anything.

03:38.677 --> 03:40.759
Pretty much just, uh, Vince
and me these days—

03:40.887 --> 03:43.754
newspaper business,
you know.

03:43.890 --> 03:46.973
- I'd like to start in, say,
uh, a week or two.

03:47.102 --> 03:50.515
l have a few things
I need to wrap up first.

03:56.528 --> 03:58.689
I'll be in touch.

04:03.660 --> 04:05.161
- You want anything else?

04:05.287 --> 04:06.493
- No, lthink, uh—

04:06.621 --> 04:08.486
I think I've had about enough,
thank you.

04:08.623 --> 04:09.908
I couldn't eat
another bite.

04:16.923 --> 04:18.003
- You all right, Chief?

04:18.133 --> 04:19.748
- Yeah, everything's fine.
Thank you.

04:21.803 --> 04:24.840
- Like to see a menu?

04:24.973 --> 04:28.465
- I'll have what he had—
two of them.

04:28.602 --> 04:30.058
How you been, Garland?

04:30.187 --> 04:31.802
- I didn't hear
you were out.

04:31.938 --> 04:33.849
- You wouldn't have thought
they would've let me out

04:33.982 --> 04:35.438
after your testimony.

04:37.861 --> 04:39.317
- You go ahead
and eat your dinner

04:39.446 --> 04:40.356
and drink your drink,

04:40.489 --> 04:41.695
and then I want you
out of here.

04:41.823 --> 04:43.905
I want you gone from Haven.

04:44.034 --> 04:45.990
I want you gone
from the entire state of Maine.

04:46.119 --> 04:48.280
Do you understand me?
- Can't do that.

04:48.413 --> 04:50.995
I have a few things I need
to take care of right here.

04:51.124 --> 04:52.830
- Either you're gone
by tonight,

04:52.959 --> 04:54.995
or I'll have
your parole violated,

04:55.128 --> 04:57.244
and you'll be back
in Shawshank tomorrow.

04:57.380 --> 04:58.540
It's your choice.

05:01.468 --> 05:03.379
Chief Wuornos.

05:03.512 --> 05:04.843
- What?

05:04.971 --> 05:06.836
- You either kill me now

05:06.973 --> 05:10.511
or get the hell away
from my table.

05:17.025 --> 05:18.936
- You heard what I said.

05:30.080 --> 05:33.447
[rumbling]

05:41.675 --> 05:44.542
[dramatic music]

05:44.678 --> 05:52.676
